data.enText: a way that you follow to get from one place to another
Which is the best route to take?

data.chText: 建议驾驶者换一条路线。
data.enText: Motorists are advised to find an alternative route.
a coastal route

data.chText: 从佛罗伦萨到罗马的最快捷的路线
data.enText: the quickest route from Florence to Rome
an escape route

data.chText: （公共汽车和列车等的）常规路线，固定线路
data.enText: a fixed way along which a bus, train, etc. regularly travels or goods are regularly sent
The house is not on a bus route .
shipping routes
a cycle route (= a path that is only for cyclists )
a particular way of achieving sth
the route to success
used before the number of a main road in the US
Route 66
routing
or
routeing
routed
routed
to send sb/sth by a particular route

data.chText: 卫星向全球各地传递信息。
data.enText: Satellites route data all over the globe.

means: (公共汽车和列车等的)常规路线，固定线路

ex.chText: 公路
ex.enText: highway

ex.chText: 高速公路
ex.enText: motorway

ex.chText: 铁路
ex.enText: railway

ex.chText: 他问路人去邮局的路。
ex.enText: He asked a passer-by the way to the post office.

ex.chText: 有一辆卡车挡住了路。
ex.enText: There was a truck blocking the way.

ex.chText: 这是通往那个小村庄的道路。
ex.enText: This is the way to the small village.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，含义广泛，可指任何形式的路，也常和其他词构成复合词。

ex.chText: 我的地址是：美国纽约第5大街211号。
ex.enText: My address is 211, Ave. 5, New York, USA.

ex.chText: 人们喜欢沿巴黎的大街散步。
ex.enText: People love to walk down the avenues of Paris.

ex.chText: 她喜欢沿着林阴道散步。
ex.enText: She likes to walk along the avenue.

synonyms.bx: 指城镇中长而宽的大街，通常为南北走向；英国英语中则指通向大房子的林阴道。

ex.chText: 车道两边是两行大树。
ex.enText: There are two lines of big trees on both sides of the drive.

ex.chText: 他把送货车停在小别墅的私人车道上。
ex.enText: He pulled up the delivery van at the cottage drive.

ex.chText: 我们不能把车停在这条私人车道上。
ex.enText: We can't park the car on this drive.

synonyms.bx: 指连接私人住宅与外部街道的车道，通常专供私人车辆通行。

ex.chText: 离开那个镇子的公路有两条。
ex.enText: There are two highways out of the town.

ex.chText: 这条公路与那条铁路平行。
ex.enText: The highway runs parallel with the railway.

synonyms.bx: 指连接两个城镇的主干道。

ex.chText: 由于大雾，高速公路关闭了。
ex.enText: The motorway has been closed due to the thick fog.

ex.chText: 沿着高速公路可以看到很多警示牌。
ex.enText: You can see many warning signs along the motorway.

synonyms.bx: 尤指城市之间的高速公路。

ex.chText: 你注意到草地上那条被踩得坑坑洼洼的小径了吗？
ex.enText: Have you noticed the well-worn path across the grass?

ex.chText: 他们顺着小路来到那个村子。
ex.enText: They followed the path to the village.

ex.chText: 我们沿着小路行走，欣赏着自然风光。
ex.enText: We walked along the path, enjoying the natural scenery.

ex.chText: 他们只得在丛林中开出一条小路。
ex.enText: They had to cut out a path through the jungle.

synonyms.bx: 通常指小道、小路、小径，特别是田间、林间常由人或牲畜走出来的小径。

ex.chText: 这条路是上周正式通车的。
ex.enText: This road was formally opened last week.

ex.chText: 过马路的时候再小心也不为过。
ex.enText: You cannot be too careful while crossing the road.

ex.chText: 在人行道上走要比在马路中间走安全。
ex.enText: It's safer to walk on the pavement than in the road.

ex.chText: 那个女人在结冰的路上滑了一跤，摔断了腿。
ex.enText: The woman slipped on the icy road and broke her leg.

synonyms.bx: 词义广泛，多指供车辆、行人或马匹等使用的平坦大道，也指旁边有建筑物的街道。

ex.chText: 我们已选定了要走的路线。
ex.enText: We've decided on the route to take.

ex.chText: 你进城最好走这条道。
ex.enText: You'd better take this route to town.

ex.chText: 这是去底特律最快的路线。
ex.enText: It's the quickest route to Detroit.

ex.chText: 专机没有按通常的商业航线飞行。
ex.enText: The special plane did not fly the usual commercial route.

synonyms.bx: 指从某处到另一处的路线，或公共汽车、火车、轮船、飞机等的固定路线或航线。

ex.chText: 你去过这条商业街吗？
ex.enText: Have you ever been to this shopping street?

ex.chText: 这里曾经是一条安静的居民街。
ex.enText: This used to be a quiet residential street.

synonyms.bx: 指城镇中的道路，其一侧或两侧通常有房屋、商店等建筑物。

ex.zh: 最短的路线（或航线）；最快的途径

tr: an open way (generally public) for travel or transportation
an established line of travel or access

example: divert the low voltage to the engine cylinders

tr: send documents or materials to appropriate destinations

value.boxr_value: Pronounced /ruːt/ or /raʊt/ in American English. 在美国英语中读作/ruːt/ 或 /raʊt/。

value.def: A route is a way from one place to another.

example.ex: ...the most direct route to the town centre...
example.tran: 到市中心最直接的路线

example.ex: All escape routes were blocked by armed police...
example.tran: 所有逃跑的路都被武警封锁了。

example.ex: Tens of thousands lined the route from Dublin airport.
example.tran: 从都柏林机场出来的道路两边站着数万人。

value.def: A bus, air, or shipping route is the way between two places along which buses, planes, or ships travel regularly.

example.tran: 去往日本的主要航运线路

value.def: In the United States, Route is used in front of a number in the names of main roads between major cities.

example.tran: 580号公路的百老汇－韦伯斯特出口

value.def: Your route is the series of visits you make to different people or places, as part of your job.

example.ex: He began cracking open big blue tins of butter cookies and feeding the dogs on his route...
example.tran: 他打开装黄油饼干的蓝色大罐子，开始沿路给狗喂食。

example.ex: They would go out on his route and check him.
example.tran: 他们会到他那里走访一下，看看他的情况。

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 round, rounds

value.def: You can refer to a way of achieving something as a route .

example.ex: Researchers are trying to get at the same information through an indirect route...
example.tran: 研究人员正试图通过间接的途径获得相同的信息。

example.ex: Buying the best is as sure a route to success in investment as in any other field.
example.tran: 和其他领域一样，投资领域获得成功的途径也是买进最佳商品。

value.def: If vehicles, goods, or passengers are routed in a particular direction, they are made to travel in that direction.

example.ex: Double-stack trains are taking a lot of freight that used to be routed via trucks...
example.tran: 以往由卡车运送的很多货物现在都改用双层列车运送了。

example.ex: Approaching cars will be routed into two lanes.
example.tran: 驶来的车辆会分流到两条车道。

value.tran: 按特定路线发送(车辆、货物或乘客)

value.def: If telephone calls or other electronic signals are routed in a particular way, the signals are sent through a particular series of connections.

example.ex: ...plans to route every emergency call in Britain through just three telephone exchanges.
example.tran: 只通过3次电话转接来传送英国境内所有紧急呼叫的计划

value.tran: 以…线路发送(电话或其他电子信号)

value.def: En route to a place means on the way to that place. En route is sometimes spelled on toute in non-standard English.

example.ex: They have arrived in London en route to the United States...
example.tran: 他们已经到达伦敦，正在前往美国的途中。

example.ex: One of the bags was lost en route.
example.tran: 其中一个包在途中丢失了。

value.tran: 在途中，沿途(在不规范英语中有时拼作on route)

value.def: Journalists sometimes use en route when they are mentioning an event that happened as part of a longer process or before another event.

example.ex: The German set three tournament records and equalled two others en route to grabbing golf's richest prize.
example.tran: 那个德国人在获得高尔夫球赛最高奖金的同时刷新了3项锦标赛纪录，平了其他两项纪录。

value.tran: （新闻用语）作为（较长进程）的一部分，在…之前

value.def: If you go the route, you do something fully or continue with a task until you have completely finished.

example.ex: They have gone the route, in many cases, of just big — big bowls, big statues, big masks, big everything.
example.tran: 在很多情况下，他们从头到尾都只做大的东西——大碗，大雕像，大面具，所有东西都是大的。

value.tran: 把事情进行到底;贯彻始终
